The paper discusses the use of neural networks for position evaluation in board games, specifically Othello. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the architecture and learning of the neural networks, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also mentions the use of evolutionary algorithms to optimize the networks, which falls under game theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper mentions the use of computer vision techniques to represent the game board, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV).
